Firewalls: to improve security of the system.

ssl: improves security bt encrypting clients requests used to safeguard sensitive info like passwords. The encryption can only be decrypted by the target server.

https: far more secure than http.

monitors: to observe the ongoings in our system. They help in error detections.

	issues
 ======

Having only one database incharge of writes is a problem as if in a scenario where that database is down, the website would lose a major functionality.

As all the servers have the same component, if tgere's an error it'd affect all the servers as they are identical in structure.
